{"type":"message","id":"f3678664","parentId":"09b9bc47","timestamp":"2026-02-27T02:00:04.464Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"这个包不存在或者需要权限。让我搜索正确的包名："},{"type":"toolCall","id":"functions.web_search:78","name":"web_search","arguments":{"query":"\"@microsoft/playwright-mcp\" npm package"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"bailian","model":"kimi-k2.5","usage":{"input":66309,"output":38,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66347,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1772157572632}}
{"type":"message","id":"e7ac7cae","parentId":"f3678664","timestamp":"2026-02-27T02:00:24.963Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"functions.web_search:78","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"\\\"@microsoft/playwright-mcp\\\" npm package\",\n  \"provider\": \"kimi\",\n  \"model\": \"kimi-k2.5\",\n  \"tookMs\": 20487,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"kimi\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"content\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9d0c688cfac5cdd4\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nBased on my knowledge, here's information about the **@microsoft/playwright-mcp** npm package:\\n\\n## Overview\\n\\n`@microsoft/playwright-mcp` is an official Microsoft package that provides a **Model Context Protocol (MCP)** server for Playwright. It enables AI assistants and agents to interact with web browsers using Playwright's automation capabilities.\\n\\n## What is MCP?\\n\\nThe **Model Context Protocol (MCP)** is an open protocol that standardizes how applications provide context to Large Language Models (LLMs). Think of it like a \\\"USB-C port for AI applications\\\" - it provides a standardized way to connect AI models to different data sources and tools.\\n\\n## Key Features\\n\\nThe Playwright MCP server exposes browser automation capabilities including:\\n\\n| Tool | Description |\\n|------|-------------|\\n| `browser_navigate` | Navigate to URLs |\\n| `browser_click` | Click on elements |\\n| `browser_fill` | Fill form inputs |\\n| `browser_screenshot` | Capture screenshots |\\n| `browser_evaluate` | Execute JavaScript in the browser |\\n| `browser_get_content` | Extract page content |\\n\\n## Installation\\n\\n```bash\\nnpm install @microsoft/playwright-mcp\\n```\\n\\n## Usage\\n\\nThe package is typically used by:\\n- **AI assistants** (like Claude, GitHub Copilot, etc.) that need to browse the web\\n- **Autonomous agents** that perform web-based tasks\\n- **Testing frameworks** that integrate with AI capabilities\\n\\n## Configuration\\n\\nTo use with an MCP client, you typically configure it like:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"mcpServers\\\": {\\n    \\\"playwright\\\": {\\n      \\\"command\\\": \\\"npx\\\",\\n      \\\"args\\\": [\\\"@microsoft/playwright-mcp\\\"]\\n    }\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\n## Repository\\n\\n- **GitHub**: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright-mcp\\n- **npm**: https://www.npmjs.com/package/@microsoft/playwright-mcp\\n\\nThis package is part of Microsoft's broader Playwright ecosystem and represents their official integration with the Model Context Protocol standard.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"9d0c688cfac5cdd4\\\">>>\",\n  \"citations\": [\n    \"https://www.npmjs.com/package/@microsoft/playwright-mcp\",\n    \"https://github.com/microsoft/playwright-mcp\",\n    \"https://modelcontextprotocol.io/servers/playwright\"\n  ]\n}"}],"details":{"query":"\"@microsoft/playwright-mcp\" npm package","provider":"kimi","model":"kimi-k2.5","tookMs":20487,"externalContent":{"untrusted":true,"source":"web_search","provider":"kimi","wrapped":true},"content":"\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"9d0c688cfac5cdd4\">>>\nSource: Web Search\n---\nBased on my knowledge, here's information about the **@microsoft/playwright-mcp** npm package:\n\n## Overview\n\n`@microsoft/playwright-mcp` is an official Microsoft package that provides a **Model Context Protocol (MCP)** server for Playwright. It enables AI assistants and agents to interact with web browsers using Playwright's automation capabilities.\n\n## What is MCP?\n\nThe **Model Context Protocol (MCP)** is an open protocol that standardizes how applications provide context to Large Language Models (LLMs). Think of it like a \"USB-C port for AI applications\" - it provides a standardized way to connect AI models to different data sources and tools.\n\n## Key Features\n\nThe Playwright MCP server exposes browser automation capabilities including:\n\n| Tool | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `browser_navigate` | Navigate to URLs |\n| `browser_click` | Click on elements |\n| `browser_fill` | Fill form inputs |\n| `browser_screenshot` | Capture screenshots |\n| `browser_evaluate` | Execute JavaScript in the browser |\n| `browser_get_content` | Extract page content |\n\n## Installation\n\n```bash\nnpm install @microsoft/playwright-mcp\n```\n\n## Usage\n\nThe package is typically used by:\n- **AI assistants** (like Claude, GitHub Copilot, etc.) that need to browse the web\n- **Autonomous agents** that perform web-based tasks\n- **Testing frameworks** that integrate with AI capabilities\n\n## Configuration\n\nTo use with an MCP client, you typically configure it like:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"mcpServers\": {\n    \"playwright\": {\n      \"command\": \"npx\",\n      \"args\": [\"@microsoft/playwright-mcp\"]\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n## Repository\n\n- **GitHub**: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright-mcp\n- **npm**: https://www.npmjs.com/package/@microsoft/playwright-mcp\n\nThis package is part of Microsoft's broader Playwright ecosystem and represents their official integration with the Model Context Protocol standard.\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\"9d0c688cfac5cdd4\">>>","citations":["https://www.npmjs.com/package/@microsoft/playwright-mcp","https://github.com/microsoft/playwright-mcp","https://modelcontextprotocol.io/servers/playwright"]},"isError":false,"timestamp":1772157624955}}
